snippet.title: Thalaivan Oruvan - Santhosh Narayanan, ofRO, SVDP, The Indian Choral Ensemble | Coke Studio Bharat
snippet.description:
"Thalaivan Oruvan “is an anthem for those who rise, not for power, but for purpose. It is for the people who choose courage over comfort & conviction over control. It carries the pulse of a new generation that believes strength is shared & not shown off.

Santhosh Narayanan brings that emotion to life with a composition that feels raw & powerful. ofRO & SVDP’s verses hit hard, honest, & real, and when The Indian Choral Ensemble joins in, forty voices rise as one, turning the song into something larger than all of us.

This is what rising feels like, not alone, but together.
This is Thalaivan.

Listen now: https://UMGI.lnk.to/ThalaivanOruvan

snippet.description:
For centuries, poets have given voice to the human heart, shaping the language of love. #ArzKiyaHai carries that legacy forward as an intimate tribute rooted in India’s poetic tradition, embracing the unguarded honesty of speaking your heart. At its helm is India’s most popular independent artist, Anuv Jain, pairing delicate guitar work with achingly tender vocals that distill this very emotion into melody. Joining him is Indian electronic duo Lost Stories working their magic on the production of the track as well as performing on the harmonium.

#IshqBawla is a Haryanvi head-nod to love, taking notes from centuries of folklore's most dramatic love stories. More than just a song, it's a reflection on the universal experience of heartbreak, reimagined with a contemporary spirit - think of it as your hype track for moving on and leveling up.
Haryanvi rapper Dhanda Nyoliwala delivers a compelling performance, weaving relatable narratives with his signature cadence. He's joined by Xvir Grewal, whose melodic interpretation adds another layer of depth to the exploration of love and loss. The production is a vibrant fusion of modern sounds and traditional Haryanvi instrumentation, featuring the distinctive textures of the Deru, Bugchu and Ghada, creating a sonic landscape that is both familiar and refreshingly new

Listen to Ishq Bawla : https://umgi.lnk.to/IshqBawla

snippet.title: Coke Studio Bharat | PUNJAB VEKH KE | Thiarajxtt X Gulab Sidhu X Jassa Dhillon X Raaginder
snippet.description:
#PunjabVekhKe is the echo of generations past, reverberating through the present – a song of dedication, perseverance, and the relentless pursuit of excellence, all fueled by an unshakeable pride in tradition and heritage, the legacy carried within.
The spirit of community is the lifeblood of Punjab - depicted through these communal spaces, these sacred grounds, are where generations have honed not only our strength, discipline, and resilience, but also our values and sense of belonging – the cornerstones of our identity.
Versatile vocalist @gulabsidhumusic and singer-rapper @JassaDhillon1  lead the charge with mesmerizing vocals that touch the heart, with lyricist Mehak Sidhu crafting authentically Punjabi verses that resonate with truth. Producer @thiarajxtt  delivers a groove that moves the soul, while violinist @raaginder  brings his unique vision to the mix, adding a layer of magic.

snippet.title: Coke Studio Bharat | HOLO LOLO | Shankuraj Konwar X Shalmali Kholgade
snippet.description:
Across cultures, resilience and wisdom are often passed down through generations, shaping how we navigate adulthood. Inspired by the famed Moran community, #HoloLolo is a soulful track performed by Assam local #shankurajkonwar, as he tells the story of the challenges of navigating adulthood along with #shalmalikholgade, who brings her unique perspective. A variety of cultural instruments - namely the toka, gogona, and siphung, play an integral role in the composition, bringing alive the sounds of Assam, elevated with supporting electronic soundscapes.

Listen to HOLO LOLO - http://umgindia.lnk.to/HoloLolo

localized.description:
Across cultures, resilience and wisdom are often passed down through generations, shaping how we navigate adulthood. Inspired by the famed Moran community, #HoloLolo is a soulful track performed by Assam local #shankurajkonwar, as he tells the story of the challenges of navigating adulthood along with #shalmalikholgade, who brings her unique perspective. A variety of cultural instruments - namely the toka, gogona, and siphung, play an integral role in the composition, bringing alive the sounds of Assam, elevated with supporting electronic soundscapes.
